      • InteractionModel

        public InteractionModel()

      • InteractionModel

        public InteractionModel(int sampleSize,
                        int numberOfTerms)
        Initialize object by setting the observed values size. Per QTL for each sample the observed values are each term of the linear model. E.g. if the model is y = mono% + neut% + mono%:GT, the observedValues are [mono%, neut%, mono% * GT]
        Parameters:
        sampleSize - number of samples
        numberOfTerms - number of terms that the interaction model has

      • getObservedValues

        public double[][] getObservedValues()
        Get the observed values. Per QTL for each sample the observed values are each term of the linear model. E.g. if the model is y = mono% + neut% + mono%:GT, the observedValues are [mono%, neut%, mono% * GT]
        Returns:
        Matrix of observed values

      • addCelltypeVariablesIndex

        public void addCelltypeVariablesIndex(int[] values)
        Add the index of the celltype variables of the linear model e.g. the index of the celltype% and celltype%:GT of the model. If y = neut% + mono% + eos% + neut%:GT + eos%:GT celltypeTerms = [[0,3],[1],[2,4] This can be used to sum up the Beta * variable per cell type
        Parameters:
        values - The index of the celltype variables of the linear model

      • getCelltypeVariablesIndex

        public java.util.List<int[]> getCelltypeVariablesIndex()
        Get the index of the celltype variables of the linear model e.g. the index of the celltype% and celltype%:GT of the model. If y = neut% + mono% + eos% + neut%:GT + eos%:GT celltypeTerms = [[0,3],[1],[2,4] This can be used to sum up the Beta * variable per cell type
        Returns:
        The indices of the celltype variables of the linear model

      • calculateSumOfSquaresNNLS

        public void calculateSumOfSquaresNNLS(double[] expressionValues)
                               throws java.lang.IllegalAccessException
        Calculate the sum of squares, using Non-Negative Linear Regression, given a y expression vector with y ~ model. Remove of the intercept (equivalent to y ~ model -1 in R) is hard-code in This uses NNLS from Rochester Institute of technology. Documention here: https://www.cs.rit.edu/~ark/pj/doc/edu/rit/numeric/NonNegativeLeastSquares.html Can download JAR from: https://www.cs.rit.edu/~ark/pj.shtml#installed
        Parameters:
        expressionValues - Vector of expression values
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalAccessException - Exception thrown when observed values can't be retrieved
